Add two variants of make targets for e2e-tests

The default one 'test-e2e' starts with a clean slate ie. it removes
existing virtualenvs and sets them up again before running the tests.

The 'test-e2e-quick' reuses the existing virtualenvs (and hence runs
faster).

Bump version to 1.0.0
Improve README for upcoming beta release

Update README

Improved examples and text.

Also added docs/example-requirements.txt which is used for setting up
the environment for examples in the README.

Fix tests on python 2.7, 3.4 and 3.5

The tests pass on python>=3.6 but the behaviour is different on older
versions.

Update examples in README

Also mentioned `pipgrip` under alternate tools.
Update README
Update and fix Makefile for new test suites
Fix and simplify tox.ini

Refactor PackageDAG code for reusing the node index/mapping

Earlier the rendering functions eg. 'render_text', 'render_json_tree'
were constructing their own node index/mapping. Now they are using the
one already existing in the tree instance.

To facilitate this, the 'PackageDAG' class has been extended with a
'sort' method that returns a new DAG of the same type but with it's
'_obj' dict sorted alphabetically by the node key. This the tree can
be sorted without converting it into a plain OrderedDict.
Rewrite 'render_text' tests using pytest.mark.parametrize

Delete old code

This code was only referenced in the old integration test suite, which
is now deleted.

Remove old integration tests

All the tests in the old integration test suite are now replaced with
mock-based unit tests. For actual pip/setuptools integration tests, we
have e2e-tests. Hence the entire old integration test suite along with
it's virtualenv/fixture files can be deleted from the repo.

Refactor code to render cyclic deps as text and add tests

Defined a function 'render_cycles_text' to list the cyclic deps. The
dependencies are now listed in alphabetical order of the package
that's creating the cycle (2nd item in the tuple).

Added tests for this codepath.

Refactor the cyclic deps function

The new version returns the same result ie. a 3-tuple but the last
item is the an instance of ReqPackage representing the cyclic
dependency instead of a DistPackage.

It also constructs an index for looking up cycles which might improve
the performance at the cost of memory.
Enforce alphabetical order when listing conflicts

Refactor code to render conflicts as text and add tests

Defined a function to render conflicting deps as text for ease of
testing and added tests.
Add tests for cyclic_deps function
Add tests for conflicting_deps function
Add unit tests for render_text function
Install the graphviz apt-package and graphviz lib in travis conf

Fix profile based integration tests

No change in code. The expected output files need to be fixed due to
unpinned dependencies (both transient and specified in
requirements.txt)

Add tests for argparse parser

These are copied from test_integration.py (to be removed once all
unit/mocked tests are copied to test_pipdeptree.py)
Add tests for graph outputs
